South African actor John Kani walked the red carpet in Los Angeles on Monday night at the premiere of his new film, Murder Mystery. The film, which will be available on Netflix from 14 June, also stars Adam Sandler, Jennifer Aniston and Luke Evans. Murder Mystery centres on a NYC cop (Adam) who finally takes his wife (Jennifer) on a long promised European trip, a chance meeting on the flight gets them invited to an intimate family gathering on the Super Yacht of elderly billionaire Malcolm Quince (Terence Stamp). When Quince is murdered, they become the prime suspects in a modern-day whodunit. John takes on the role of  cop Colonel Ulenga. Kani is no stranger to Hollywood having starred in last year's blockbuster  hit Black Planther alongside his son Athandwa. The premiere for the new Netflix movie 'Murder Mystery' took place in Los Angeles last night. The film stars @adamsandler, Jennifer Aniston, and South African acting legend John Kani. South Africans can stream the flick on Netflix from 14 June! (??: @netflixsa) A post shared by  Channel24 (@channel24_sa) on Jun 11, 2019 at 6:51am PDT   The premiere for the new Netflix movie 'Murder Mystery' took place in Los Angeles last night. The film stars @adamsandler, Jennifer Aniston, and South African acting legend John Kani. South Africans can stream the flick on Netflix from 14 June! (??: @netflixsa) A post shared by  Channel24 (@channel24_sa) on Jun 11, 2019 at 6:50am PDT 